ithin the Vedas, Puranas, Agamas etc. Broadly s=\r\npeaking such sacred chants can be categorised as mantras, stotras, kavachas=\r\n, dhyanams etc. Some stotras too are also treated as mahamantras and mantra=\r\ns.  The Samhita portion of the Vedas too is referred to as mantras.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt;=\r\n &gt; 2.\tUndoubtedly mantras and stotras have to be chanted in the original. R=\r\neading a translation is not even comparable to chanting the original chant.=\r\n So far it is fine.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; 3.\tWhilst mantra, stotra and kavacha are all b=\r\nased on Sabda/Vak, tradition makes a distinction between them.\n&gt; &gt;      \n&gt; =\r\n&gt; 4.\tAs per the traditional view one doesn&#39;t need to be initiated to chant =\r\na stotra or dhyanam. The case is not the same with most mantras. Mantras co=\r\nntaining bijaksharas, agamic mantras, mantras of Mahavidyas etc need initia=\r\ntion. This is the traditional view. Mantras from the Veda Samhita are not t=\r\nhe same as these other mantras that need initiation, which are generally re=\r\nferred to as Agamic/Tantrik mantras. Whatever you call these mantras the ac=\r\ntual idea is that these mantras are integral parts of larger and distinct s=\r\npiritual specialities that need initiation, as in the case of Mahavidyas su=\r\nch as Kali or Sri.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; 5.\tVishnusahasranama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya =\r\nhrdayam etc do not need initiation as they fall under stotra category only.=\r\n Lalitasahasranama and Devi Mahatmyam are traditionally viewed not MERELY a=\r\ns stotras or parts of puranas. They have a larger status as integral parts =\r\nof a Mahavidya sadhana. Chanting them without initiation is not recommended=\r\n especially when the reader combines the navarna or shodashi mantras too as=\r\n an integral part of the chanting.\n&gt; &gt;            \n&gt; &gt; 6.\tI know from perso=\r\nnal interaction that acharyas belonging to both Kanchi as well as Sringeri =\r\nparamparas recommend initiation for both the sadhanas of Sri Sri Chandi and=\r\n Sri Vidya along with their respective NAVAKSHARI AND SHODASAKSHARI mantras=\r\n which are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB (ANGA) of the sadhana. Acharyas of b=\r\noth these traditions hold that one needs to be initiated to chant the Navar=\r\nna as well as shodashakshari mantras.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; 7.\tRecapping my earlier sta=\r\nnce, Devi Mahatmyam is a great text that has an independent status by itsel=\r\nf as part of a Mahavidya. It is simultaneously a Mahavidya, a Yogasastra as=\r\n well as an Advaitic text in the spirit of the Upanishads. ***As a Mahavidy=\r\na the Navakshari is an integral part of Sri Sri Chandi path***. Thus tradit=\r\nion holds that one needs to be initiated to chant it. However if one wishes=\r\n to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sacred myth aspects of the Devi Mahatm=\r\nyam, , reading the sacred myth in the vernacular has been recommended in my=\r\n write-up, as chanting the original along with the navakshari  amounts to p=\r\nracticing the sadhana of a Mahavidya. In that case it is recommended to be =\r\ninitiated and go through the specialised sadhanas properly under guidance.\n=\r\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; 8.\tArguably if an uninitiated person reads the Devi Mahatmyam in =\r\nthe original Sanskrit as part of the *Pauranik* approach and not as a Mahav=\r\nidya, it has an inherent problem in our times.  The problem with attempting=\r\n to do a parayana of Devi Mahatmyam from texts alone (without initiation) i=\r\ns that most readers inadvertently end up also chanting the Navarna mantra o=\r\nr stotras such as the Siddhakunjika stotram which too contain the bijakshar=\r\nas.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; 9.\tI you carefully peruse my write-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, =\r\nforget translating, nowhere do I put down the Navarna mantra even in writin=\r\ng. Neither have I attempted to write a commentary on it. Translations of ma=\r\nntras do not have the power of the original mantra as Sabda or Vak. However=\r\n it is recommended to know the essence or import (artha) of the mantra and =\r\nits sadhana while chanting it. Infact `artha&#39; is the import, the essence of=\r\n `Vak&#39;, not a translation! \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; 10.\tFor those who are already doing Sr=\r\ni Sri Chandi path without initiation, there is no need to worry or be confu=\r\nsed. There has to be a certain level of samskara to be attracted to Sri Sri=\r\n Chandi path itself. We all have it. Otherwise we would not be doing it (in=\r\nitiation or no initiation). Please keep doing whatever you are doing. Just =\r\nbe cautious not to do sakama sadhana. As Narasimha garu has rightly pointed=\r\n out it is better to just do the sadhana WITHOUT asking for any favours or =\r\nresults. That attitude itself will reduce a lot of the potential problem. T=\r\nhings will happen on their own accord in the natural flow. Leave the rest t=\r\no the compassionate Goddess.              \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; Hope the above pointers=\r\n help in clearing any confusion.  \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; Regards,\n&gt; &gt; Satya Prakash     =\r\n           \n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; --- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, h=\r\n ramalingam &lt;hramalingam@&gt; wrote:\n&gt; &gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; &gt; Namaste everybody\n&gt; &gt; &gt; I wan=\r\nt to share one anecdote happened in front of Kanchi Maha Sannidanam Sri\n&gt; &gt;=\r\n &gt; Sri Chandrasekara Bharathi Swamigal\n&gt; &gt; &gt; When Swamigal was staying in a=\r\n camp near Mysore in Karnataka One day all the\n&gt; &gt; &gt; learned persons male a=\r\nnd female alike\n&gt; &gt; &gt; requested Swamigal to translate Sri Vishnu SahasraNam=\r\nam in kannada language\n&gt; &gt; &gt; so that they can chant knowing the meaning ful=\r\nly.\n&gt; &gt; &gt; Swamigal didn&#39;t reply to this request which was made early in the=\r\n morning.\n&gt; &gt; &gt; Later in the